Kindergarten is also a part of the office that has included architects.
the administrative building Avriopoint of Brno is the new headquarters of Arch. Design.
No one could have expected it to also be home to a mini-kindergarten with everything you need - color walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October last year, can visit the children of Arch. design employees.
The Arch. Design. architectonic project company whose workshops have produced a large number of buildings in Brno, has imagined its mini-corporate kindergarten school since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, especially the age of children, and it was important for women architects and project leaders to return to work quickly.
At the same time as reduced-time employment contracts, kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Manufacturers and architects have the opportunity to combine work with care for children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design.themselves who imagined this kindergarten school and with the support of management they were able to obtain an staffing from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-kindergarten is financed through the European Social Fund through the operational human resources programme and the State budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to funding allocations (up to 2.8 million Czech kroons), they were able to purchase equipment and equipment and after two years to provide qualified personnel as well as start-up.
After the use of the funding allocation (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini-kindergarten on its own funds.
The project was prepared for one year, and it was Economy rating that helped make the application for staffing.
Care for children is provided by qualified staff, all day long a nurse and kindergarten teacher care for children. Children can go to kindergarten without age limit but they have more than three years for the most part.
As it is a "mini-kindergarten" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more that replace each other.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use the school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although individual care and education are involved, the mini-kindergarten programme is comparable to that for pre-school education.
Children do not just play it, but quality education is also provided - from the beginning to the preparation for school schools, English is taught.
