Parents therefore use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty between the employee and the employer is created.
Arch.Design.has thus registered as one of the companies that offer a prime of choice for the recruitment of new employees and that are friendly to the family and through this program reinforces HR marketing.
The bone house fascins again after 100 years. Take a look in Gaudi's interior.
The toe looks like the back of a prehistoric saurian, the staircase with a spine of dinosaur and the balconies with open fish gulls.
This is the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona of the architect Antoni Gaudi.
Because of its organic forms, the house received from the premises the nickname of Bone House.
Organic forms, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaics, façade recalling scales and everywhere present curves, this is all that is ypic for Antoni Gaudi's Art Nouveau.
The front facade of the house runs its dream lines, its pleasant colors and textures that remind nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation we see geometry, rhythm and order thought with precision.
In the night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brilliance of the colors is strengthened.
The enroulement and torsion of the shapes also appear in the interior with the same measure.
The wood is a wave copy of the window frames, balustrades, decorative elements of the doors, eilleton and lamelles.
The Battlo house, which stands in the Eixample district in the Passeig merchant street of Gracia at number 43, was born of the construction of a house of 1877 by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a rich entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of the old construction and the construction of another new one, but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multiple house was not thought by Gaudi alone.
Architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It was precisely on his project that the decorations for a representation apartment of the owner of the building and the use of the mosaics for the façade were born.
For the façade also worked other artists and creators.
The joint work on Casa Battlo's plans began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol has been involved in the construction of the house of Gaudi Casa Mila and the Guell Park in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The premises overnamed the hot house just after its finishing because of its organic forms "the Bone House."
Others, in view of the specific window opening mechanism, called it "the bypass house."
It is said that at the top of the building there is a sword similar to that of Saint Georges the boss of Catalonia.
Other elements of construction sculpture contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi has thought for the house a unique system in its central heating time, with ventilation vents and typical chimneys.
Their 45-degree inclination seems weird.
During the creation of Gaudi absolutely did not comply with the construction guidelines of then and did not let themselves be impeded by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained the building permit from the city, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the finishing the municipal council was horrified and asked for changes.
For example, the members of the municipal council were not pleased that the pillars of the construction were encroaching on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but on the contrary, only 15 days after the call of the city Josep Battlo asked (and obtained satisfaction) for permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and on the third one room and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewellery.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase by which you can access an independent roof terrace.
All straight angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of reconstruction and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of space liaison.
The common part can be connected completely by opening the fairs doors and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit the private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi has received in addition new facades a non-traditional roof and two more floors.
Gaudi's game with light is also impressive, blue and white glazed tiles with which the inner courtyard is decorated and with wells of lights.
The two-color game gives maximum light in all floors of the house.
It was simply enough to bet on the principle that the white reflects more than the dark that on the contrary absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house that was registered in 2005 in the Unesco World Heritage Fund may be visited by each.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued the visits as they found it to be a lucrative company and extended the field of visits to common spaces and attic including tooded terraces.
The entry ticket in the monument is really cheap and cost 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and cardholders have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the entry price in the other Gaudi buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and visit the house completely.
