The devices to follow people are increasingly being asked by parents who want to watch their children.
Fear for their child brings more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars can be used as well to track the movement of people and help for some cases like by exmple the one of the little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a box of matches but will soon be of the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka has moved a large number of people and they have begun to seek ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
"We are trying to tell all that it is not spying but only another way to reduce the likelihood that there will be another tragedy," said Petr Pilin of MAcro Weil, who is one of the suppliers of tracing devices in the Czech market.
"I confess that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in a person's bag that is not aware of, but I have not yet met such cases."
"The majority of people are clients who really buy the product for safety reasons," says Pilin.
According to him, children should always know what purpose is used "box" and how to use it in an emergency.
The children's psychologist, Dana Bockova, draws attention to the fact that if the child doesn't want to wear something like this on him, he'll get rid of it.
'And even the smallest can show great creativity when it comes to getting rid of something on purpose when they don't want to be under control. "
"Mobile phones, which can cut like these tracing devices, have already brought parents to long expectations," says Bockova.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in the event of aggression is very questionable.
"If it is a prepared rapt, the author will do everything to ensure that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate him."
"Now it's the phone."
"As soon as the tracing equipment develops, they (the criminals) will also look for them because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
"In such cases the criminals will always be ahead of the police," said the psychologist.
It still confesses that such devices can help in an unprepared assault by a pedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, who offers tracing services for both cars and people, says that having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the case of an assault.
"The device may be set in such a way that it is in regular emission after a specified period of time."
"In the event that the aircraft is destroyed, it still remains the last position of the person concerned."
'The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately reports the position of the person who slide and is in an elongated position without moving, "says Cech.
According to him, so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after having formatted it with a special prosoftware.
The problem with the current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those carried in a pendentif of the size of an matches box or to the smallest telephone devices.
We can still lose them.
According to Pilina of Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being carried out to make devices that resemble common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the potential assailant will not be able to recognize the tracing device."
"Or he will be aware of it after some time, which will have given the police a little more time," he added.
Whether the tracing device is developed in the form of a bracelet or a pendent, it will always use the same technology as for tracing cars.
This is a combination of position acquisition systems using GPS (which is commonly used in self-avigation) and a mobile phone function that alerts the current position of a vehicle.
